## Key Features to Implement (Modern & Cost-Effective)

### Progressive Web App (PWA) Digital Library

- Build as PWA for native app-like experience without app store costs
- Implement service workers for offline reading and caching
- Use free local storage solutions (IndexedDB) for offline content
- Responsive design optimized for mobile-first experience
- Push notifications for new books, assignments, and deadlines
- Install prompts for home screen addition on mobile devices

### Advanced Search & Content Discovery

- Implement full-text search with Meilisearch for fast academic content discovery
- Use structured search with filtering by academic programs, courses, and metadata
- Auto-complete search suggestions based on indexed content and user queries
- Content categorization using structured taxonomies and manual tagging
- Rule-based content organization by academic programs and course requirements
- User-based recommendations through reading history and bookmarks tracking

### Modern Reading Experience

- Use PDF.js (free) for progressive loading and annotations
- Implement social reading features with shared highlights
- Text-to-speech using Web Speech API (free browser feature)
- Dark/light mode with customizable reading themes
- Speed reading tools and reading time estimates
- Cross-device bookmark and note synchronization

